  "image": "6558\\6558.jpg",
  "title": "Beth & Josie: EXPOSED",
  "description": "34X Award-Winning Producing Fringe Artist Beth Marshall is back headlining her own story, Paducah Cheerleader, about growing up in the Deep South of Ky. Hosted by JUICE The Trauma Clown. Raw &amp; Real Stories.",
  "credits": "<strong>Cast</strong>: Beth Marshall, Josie Nixon, JUICE The Trauma Clown, Bobby Wesley, Michael Marinaccio &amp; Guests<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Projection/Sound: Blue Estrella, Props: Josie Nixon, Lights: Rowyn Sam, Beth;s Poncho: Julianna Aberle-McClellan, Juice's Costume: Lavi McConaughey, Graphics: C-Mac The Art Wizard<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Nicole Alton<br/>",
  "website": "https://exposedstorytelling.com",
  "plain_language": "EXPOSED is a raw and honest storytelling show featuring true personal stories told in different dramatic styles. Created by Josie Nixon, it focuses on empathy, community, and healing through shared experiences. Each night opens with rotating stories, followed by the main act, Paducah Cheerleader, a powerful memoir about interracial dating in rural Kentucky. Audiences can return to hear new stories throughout the festival and even take part by submitting anonymous secrets, which are read aloud by JUICE the Trauma Clown to help build connection and understanding.",
